text.paragraph:
For patients expected to be on prolonged treatment or who take PPIs with medications such as digoxin or drugs that may cause hypomagnesemia (e.g., diuretics), health care professionals may consider monitoring magnesium levels prior to initiation of PPI treatment and periodically. [See Adverse Reactions 

                              6.2
                           )]

Concomitant administration of pantoprazole and clopidogrel in healthy subjects had no clinically important effect on exposure to the active metabolite of clopidogrel or clopidogrelinduced platelet inhibition [see 
                              Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)

                           ]. No dose adjustment of clopidogrel is necessary when administered with an approved dose of pantoprazole sodium.
